The owner of Nairobi's Ranalo Foods was shot and injured in Kasarani, Nairobi on Thursday.William Osewe was attacked by Oywa Mboya, who claimed the restaurant owner confronted him first.Mboya, a licenced firearm holder, was disarmed by police.Osewe was first rushed to AAR Healthcare at Mountain Mall before being transferred to Aga Khan Hospital.His vehicle, a white Mercedes Benz, was towed to Kasarani police station.Ranalo, popularly known as K Osewe, is where top leaders eat fish.